16/05/2003
STRASBOURG, France -- At a session of the Ministerial Committee of the Council of Europe, Croatian Foreign Minister Tonino Picula said companies in his country want to participate in the reconstruction of post-war Iraq. He said Zagreb is preparing proposals for co-operation with multinational contractors, and would join UN initiatives.
In other news, plans for Pope John Paul II's visit to Croatia are firming up. He will arrive on 5 June at the airport on the island of Krk, and will visit Rijeka, Dubrovnik, Osijek and Zadar. (HINA, HRT - 15/05/03; BBC - 09/05/03)
